President and Mrs. Potter, with their custo- mary regard for the social enjoyment of the students, have been giving Thursday afternoon receptions during the month. These have proved very enjoyable affairs and have been well attended. It is certainly a welcome change from tedious recitations and cheerless rooms to spend an hour with our courteous President and his very entertaining lady and the select company which always grace their rooms .. Those of the students who miss these recep- tions miss some of life's pleasant hours. We understand that Prof. Whitehorn has the Juniors and Sophomores in Latin next term.
